<i>didn't have to mean
cutting myself off completely.</i>

258
00:15:02.790 --> 00:15:05.160
<i>Maybe I'd been hanging
with the wrong people.</i>

259
00:15:08.880 --> 00:15:12.000
<i>Maybe I could start over
with the right person.</i>

260
00:15:14.840 --> 00:15:17.810
<i>But if I'd have known
what was going to happen.</i>

261
00:15:17.840 --> 00:15:20.180
<i>I never would have walked
through that door.</i>

262
00:15:35.650 --> 00:15:36.650
Hey...

263
00:15:37.610 --> 00:15:38.610
is everything okay?

264
00:15:41.700 --> 00:15:44.370
Clay listened to the tape about my party.

265
00:15:45.160 --> 00:15:47.870
All that bullshit Hannah said.
Of course he believes it.

266
00:15:48.870 --> 00:15:50.500
He said he wants to help me.

267
00:15:51.710 --> 00:15:53.640
So. whatever Tony did didn't work.

268
00:15:53.670 --> 00:15:54.920
Apparently not.

269
00:15:57.840 --> 00:16:01.430
If Hannah had seen something.
she would have told me. right?

270
00:16:04.260 --> 00:16:07.270
I mean. we both know
she made all that stuff up.

271
00:16:08.730 --> 00:16:09.730
Did she?

272
00:16:11.400 --> 00:16:14.690
Because that photo of her
on the slide with Justin was real.

273
00:16:15.440 --> 00:16:18.040
The "Hot or Not" list was real. so...

274
00:16:18.070 --> 00:16:19.570
maybe the rest was too.

275
00:16:28.660 --> 00:16:29.660
Jessica...

276
00:16:30.790 --> 00:16:32.290
Justin is your boyfriend.

277
00:16:33.040 --> 00:16:35.420
Who are you going to believe. him or...

278
00:16:36.510 --> 00:16:39.510
a girl who was jealous
because you were dating her ex?

279
00:16:52.560 --> 00:16:53.560
Hey.

280
00:16:53.860 --> 00:16:54.790
Hey.

281
00:16:54.820 --> 00:16:58.030
Hey. um. Justin said
you might have a little herb on you?

282
00:16:58.400 --> 00:17:00.580
What are you. <i>21 Jump Street</i>?

283
00:17:00.610 --> 00:17:02.240
Since when do you smoke at school?

284
00:17:02.570 --> 00:17:03.620
It's for a friend.

285
00:17:04.160 --> 00:17:05.200
Uh-huh.

286
00:17:05.580 --> 00:17:06.550
Okay.

287
00:17:06.580 --> 00:17:08.300
Come to my house after school.

288
00:17:08.330 --> 00:17:09.580
Nah. I kind of need it now.

289
00:17:10.210 --> 00:17:12.710
I mean. I can hook you up
with my guy here.

290
00:17:13.880 --> 00:17:17.270
Come on. I can't buy on campus.
I'm the student body president.

291
00:17:17.300 --> 00:17:19.100
I'm captain of the football team.

292
00:17:19.130 --> 00:17:21.810
The rules are different for us.
in many ways.

293
00:17:21.840 --> 00:17:22.840
You know it.

294
00:17:23.390 --> 00:17:24.390
Yeah.

295
00:17:25.680 --> 00:17:26.810
Come on...

296
00:17:26.970 --> 00:17:28.100
Fuck. All right.

297
00:17:28.310 --> 00:17:30.110
Come and see me after fifth.

298
00:17:30.140 --> 00:17:30.980
Thank you.

299
00:17:31.140 --> 00:17:32.140
You're welcome.

300
00:17:34.560 --> 00:17:36.730
You showed him the poem?

301
00:17:38.900 --> 00:17:41.000
Why on earth would you do that?

302
00:17:41.030 --> 00:17:43.750
He walked in here all self-righteous.

303
00:17:43.780 --> 00:17:48.130
telling me we needed counseling.
as if we're delusional.

304
00:17:48.160 --> 00:17:51.090
As if this whole lawsuit
is a big waste of time.

305
00:17:51.120 --> 00:17:53.970
It isn't. we're not.
and I want people to know it.

306
00:17:54.000 --> 00:17:56.720
It was our one piece of leverage. Andy!

307
00:17:56.750 --> 00:17:58.140
You showed him our hand!

308
00:17:58.170 --> 00:18:02.880
Hannah was crying out for help
right under their noses.

309
00:18:04.550 --> 00:18:06.930
And under ours. too.

310
00:18:08.010 --> 00:18:10.100
Uh... Andy. sweetie...

311
00:18:11.430 --> 00:18:15.570
you don't win a chess match

312
00:18:15.600 --> 00:18:17.870
by giving away your strategy. honey.

313
00:18:17.900 --> 00:18:20.030
I'm trying to fight back here!

314
00:18:23.030 --> 00:18:24.700
I thought that's what you wanted.

315
00:18:26.280 --> 00:18:27.740
Not like this.

316
00:18:38.630 --> 00:18:40.420
<i>Hey. Ryan. thanks for coming in.</i>

317
00:18:41.130 --> 00:18:43.970
I wanted to ask you a question
about this poem.

318
00:18:46.970 --> 00:18:47.970
Oh.

319
00:18:48.510 --> 00:18:51.030
Do you remember where it came from?

320
00:18:51.060 --> 00:18:53.180
Someone slipped it
into my locker last year.

321
00:18:53.350 --> 00:18:56.270
- Hmm.
- Yeah. I thought it was well-written.

322
00:18:57.100 --> 00:18:59.860
So you didn't actually find it on campus.

323
00:19:00.360 --> 00:19:02.570
Isn't that the whole conceit
of the magazine?

324
00:19:03.990 --> 00:19:06.910
Sometimes I get submissions anonymously.

325
00:19:08.490 --> 00:19:10.130
Why are you asking me about this?

326
00:19:10.160 --> 00:19:11.950
It seems that Hannah Baker wrote it.

327
00:19:14.750 --> 00:19:15.680
Oh. my God.

328
00:19:15.710 --> 00:19:19.130
Now her folks aren't too happy
it got passed out around campus.

329
00:19:20.040 --> 00:19:21.640
I had no idea it was Hannah's.

330
00:19:21.670 --> 00:19:24.270
Did you think maybe
the person who wrote this

331
00:19:24.300 --> 00:19:26.220
was thinking about hurting themself?

332
00:19:26.880 --> 00:19:27.940
To be honest.

333
00:19:27.970 --> 00:19:30.720
this isn't the first submission
I've received like this.

334
00:19:31.010 --> 00:19:34.180
Teenage angst. you know?
Perennially popular.

335
00:19:35.640 --> 00:19:39.950
But just because you write something
doesn't mean you're going to do it.

336
00:19:39.980 --> 00:19:41.080
True.

337
00:19:41.110 --> 00:19:42.870
But I'm afraid the administration

338
00:19:42.900 --> 00:19:45.360
