343
00:19:54.540 --> 00:19:57.630
That's unfair.
I built this magazine out of nothing.

344
00:19:57.660 --> 00:19:59.890
It's the focal point of my college apps.

345
00:19:59.920 --> 00:20:02.510
You may be asked to give testimony
about this poem.

346
00:20:02.540 --> 00:20:04.840
That could affect
your college admission too.

347
00:20:06.300 --> 00:20:07.300
I'm sorry.

348
00:20:09.220 --> 00:20:10.890
Sucks to be held accountable.

349
00:20:13.050 --> 00:20:14.050
Doesn't it?

350
00:20:15.100 --> 00:20:16.100
Excuse me?

351
00:20:25.190 --> 00:20:26.190
Hey.

352
00:20:27.650 --> 00:20:28.650
Hey.

353
00:20:30.240 --> 00:20:31.170
Marcus.

354
00:20:31.200 --> 00:20:33.750
Hi. Mr. Porter. Um. you got a moment?

355
00:20:33.780 --> 00:20:35.550
Sure. Do we have an appointment today?

356
00:20:35.580 --> 00:20:39.330
No. Mr. Porter.
but it's actually kind of urgent.

357
00:20:40.170 --> 00:20:41.170
Um...

358
00:20:41.460 --> 00:20:44.840
I'm really worried about Clay Jensen.

359
00:20:46.210 --> 00:20:49.230
<i>"I am invisible.
understand. simply because"</i>

360
00:20:49.260 --> 00:20:51.440
people refuse to see me.

361
00:20:51.470 --> 00:20:55.070
When they approach me.
they see only my surroundings.

362
00:20:55.100 --> 00:20:58.490
themselves. or figments
of their imagination...

363
00:20:58.520 --> 00:21:03.520
"indeed. everything and anything
except me."

364
