who killed herself for attention.

771
00:45:56.680 --> 00:45:58.520
I'm sorry. man.
I know she was your friend.

772
00:45:59.770 --> 00:46:01.490
And you were her first kiss.

773
00:46:01.520 --> 00:46:02.770
So she said.

774
00:46:06.520 --> 00:46:07.860
Whatever happened...

775
00:46:09.030 --> 00:46:11.190
whatever Hannah thinks happened...

776
00:46:12.990 --> 00:46:14.360
how does that help Jess now?

777
00:46:14.910 --> 00:46:17.740
What she needs. what we all need...

778
00:46:18.660 --> 00:46:20.260
is for this to be done with.

779
00:46:20.290 --> 00:46:23.040
How can she be done with this
if she doesn't know what it is?

780
00:46:32.760 --> 00:46:35.400
Dude. come on.
Leave her alone. get off her.

781
00:46:35.430 --> 00:46:38.510
- Get the fuck out of here!
- Hey. hey! Dude. dude!

782
00:46:54.740 --> 00:46:55.990
You can get me suspended.

783
00:46:57.200 --> 00:46:59.280
You can ruin my fucking life
if you want to.

784
00:46:59.950 --> 00:47:01.120
It won't change what you did.

785
00:47:03.080 --> 00:47:05.540
And sooner or later.
people are going to find out.

786
00:47:06.670 --> 00:47:09.130
People are not gonna find out.

787
00:47:09.460 --> 00:47:11.520
Why are you protecting Bryce?

788
00:47:11.550 --> 00:47:12.680
What does he have on you?

789
00:47:12.710 --> 00:47:14.880
I'm not protecting Bryce.
you little fuck!

790
00:47:17.510 --> 00:47:19.350
God. I'm protecting Jessica!

791
00:47:21.010 --> 00:47:23.450
I care more about Jessica
than I do about Hannah.

792
00:47:23.480 --> 00:47:25.560
than I do about you.
than I do about anybody else.

793
00:47:27.230 --> 00:47:28.940
All right? So just get the fuck out!

794
00:47:34.490 --> 00:47:35.530
I want my bike.

795
00:47:38.030 --> 00:47:39.030
Your bike?

796
00:47:39.990 --> 00:47:40.880
Seriously?

797
00:47:40.910 --> 00:47:43.910
Yes. you fucking asshole.
I want my bike.

798
00:47:45.910 --> 00:47:47.620
It's out back. behind the building.

799
00:47:48.460 --> 00:47:50.000
Go knock yourself out.

800
00:48:10.110 --> 00:48:11.860
- Hey.
- Hey.

801
00:48:13.780 --> 00:48:15.030
Did you find him?

802
00:48:15.530 --> 00:48:18.830
I drove around for an hour
since I called you.

803
00:48:18.860 --> 00:48:20.120
Nothing.

804
00:48:20.450 --> 00:48:22.120
Where could he be going?

805
00:48:22.330 --> 00:48:23.950
This point. who knows.

806
00:48:26.040 --> 00:48:27.430
And the weed?

807
00:48:27.460 --> 00:48:29.590
Maybe we've been looking
at the wrong warning signs.

808
00:48:29.620 --> 00:48:32.880
Maybe we don't have a suicidal kid.
we've got one with a drug problem.

809
00:48:33.210 --> 00:48:34.750
I really don't think so.

810
00:48:34.960 --> 00:48:37.230
I teach potheads.
I know what that looks like.

811
00:48:37.260 --> 00:48:38.430
It's not Clay.

812
00:48:38.840 --> 00:48:40.300
He's quite good at hiding things.

813
00:48:41.220 --> 00:48:42.770
He said he didn't know her.

814
00:48:42.800 --> 00:48:44.440
He said he didn't know her well.

815
00:48:44.470 --> 00:48:46.270
Clearly. he knew her very well.

816
00:48:46.850 --> 00:48:49.020
He is devastated.

817
00:48:49.770 --> 00:48:52.860
He feels like he's responsible somehow.

818
00:48:59.700 --> 00:49:01.070
Was she his girlfriend?

819
00:49:03.280 --> 00:49:04.700
Did he do something to her?

820
00:49:05.330 --> 00:49:06.490
Jesus. Lainie...

821
00:49:07.080 --> 00:49:08.370
what are you implying?

822
00:49:10.250 --> 00:49:12.970
I am defending a lawsuit
brought by two parents

823
00:49:13.000 --> 00:49:15.390
whose daughter was so damaged by something

824
00:49:15.420 --> 00:49:17.460
that she took her own life.

825
00:49:18.760 --> 00:49:20.270
What if our son was part of that?

826
00:49:20.300 --> 00:49:21.840
He's not capable of it.

827
00:49:22.470 --> 00:49:23.680
How do you know?

828
00:49:24.220 --> 00:49:25.260
I know.

829
00:49:33.100 --> 00:49:34.280
I have to give up the case.

830
00:49:34.310 --> 00:49:35.900
I can't take it to trial.

831
00:49:36.860 --> 00:49:38.410
To protect Clay?

832
00:49:38.440 --> 00:49:39.490
Or you and me?

833
00:49:40.700 --> 00:49:42.200
To protect all of us.

834
00:49:43.200 --> 00:49:46.280
Quitting the case
wouldn't even do that. would it?

835
00:50:38.630 --> 00:50:40.140
- Where's Justin?
- Shh. shh.

836
00:50:40.170 --> 00:50:43.010
Shh. Don't worry about him.
We're just having fun. okay?

837
00:50:43.590 --> 00:50:45.550
- What?
- Take it easy.

838
00:50:52.230 --> 00:50:53.560
What are you doing?

839
00:51:00.070 --> 00:51:01.070
Oh. my God!

840
00:51:18.130 --> 00:51:19.130
Hey.

841
00:51:19.920 --> 00:51:20.920
Hey.

842
00:51:21.250 --> 00:51:22.250
Sorry I didn't...

843
00:51:22.920 --> 00:51:24.170
didn't text you back.

844
00:51:27.220 --> 00:51:28.260
Can I come in?

845
00:51:30.310 --> 00:51:31.310
Yeah.

846
00:51:53.040 --> 00:51:54.830
We should probably talk. huh?

847
00:52:32.120 --> 00:52:33.280
Hey. Tony.

848
00:52:38.120 --> 00:52:39.250
Tony!

849
00:52:41.710 --> 00:52:42.790
Yeah.

850
00:52:44.250 --> 00:52:46.090
Your dad said I could come find you.

851
00:52:47.220 --> 00:52:48.140
You okay?

852
00:52:48.170 --> 00:52:50.130
I just talked to Justin about Jessica.

853
00:52:50.800 --> 00:52:51.800
Okay.

854
00:52:53.600 --> 00:52:55.150
How did everyone...

855
00:52:55.180 --> 00:52:56.400
how did you...

856
00:52:56.430 --> 00:52:58.070
just listen to that.

857
00:52:58.100 --> 00:53:00.030
and. like. ignore it?

858
00:53:00.060 --> 00:53:02.110
I don't think anyone ignored it. Clay.

859
00:53:02.730 --> 00:53:04.820
Why is everyone protecting Bryce?

860
00:53:05.400 --> 00:53:06.820
Why are you?

861
00:53:06.990 --> 00:53:08.250
I'm doing it for Hannah.

862
00:53:08.280 --> 00:53:10.250
Fuck that. Tony! Fuck that!

863
00:53:10.280 --> 00:53:11.740
Jessica got raped!

864
00:53:12.870 --> 00:53:16.710
And Justin's got her brainwashed.
Everyone at school is covering it up.

865
00:53:16.740 --> 00:53:19.680
- That is beyond fucked up!
- You don't know the whole story yet.

866
00:53:19.710 --> 00:53:21.220
What else do I need to know?

867
00:53:21.250 --> 00:53:24.760
You're brainwashed like the rest.
but I'm not. okay?

868
00:53:24.790 --> 00:53:27.350
And I'm not gonna sit back and do nothing

869
00:53:27.380 --> 00:53:29.520
like you and everyone else.
including Hannah.

870
00:53:29.550 --> 00:53:31.010
You need to calm down.

871
00:53:31.130 --> 00:53:34.070
She let everyone intimidate her
over and over and over.

872
00:53:34.100 --> 00:53:35.970
until she just disappeared.

873
00:53:37.720 --> 00:53:40.030
Well. not me. no. I am not giving up.

874
00:53:40.060 --> 00:53:42.270
- You're upset.
- Fucking right! Why aren't you?

875
00:53:42.980 --> 00:53:44.310
Why isn't everybody?

876
00:53:45.480 --> 00:53:47.070
Just take a breath. okay?

877
00:53:47.820 --> 00:53:49.280
Fuck you. Tony.

878
00:53:50.570 --> 00:53:52.860
- Fuck you.
- What the fuck are you doing. Clay?

879
00:53:53.530 --> 00:53:54.530
Come on!

880
00:54:01.290 --> 00:54:02.290
Fuck you.

881
00:54:02.960 --> 00:54:04.250
Fuck all of you.

882
00:54:14.430 --> 00:54:15.430
Fuck.

883
00:54:15.970 --> 00:54:16.970
Goddamn it!

884
00:54:17.430 --> 00:54:18.510
God!

885
00:55:00.560 --> 00:55:02.480
What happens if the tapes get out?

886
00:55:03.520 --> 00:55:07.200
Let's say we try and get
some justice for Jessica.

887
00:55:07.230 --> 00:55:08.230
What then?

888
00:55:08.820 --> 00:55:10.620
It's his word against a dead girl's.

889
00:55:10.650 --> 00:55:13.530
Open season on Hannah Baker
all over again.

890
00:55:13.990 --> 00:55:16.410
What if we got one person
to tell the truth?

891
00:55:17.870 --> 00:55:20.660
- I mean. just one of them.
- All right. okay. I'll make you a deal.

892
00:55:20.830 --> 00:55:22.830
Listen to the tapes. all of them.

893
00:55:23.660 --> 00:55:24.710
And then we'll talk.

894
00:55:25.460 --> 00:55:27.170
We'll do whatever we have to do.

895
00:55:27.960 --> 00:55:29.000
And you'll help me?

896
00:55:30.880 --> 00:55:31.880
Always.
